  "name": "2 Chronicles 14:2–16:14",
  "localizedName": "2 Chronicles 14:2–16:14",
  "content": [
    {
      "tiptap": {
        "type": "doc",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "paragraph",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "text",
                "text": "For many years "
              },
              {
                "type": "text",
                "marks": [
                  {
                    "type": "resourceReference",
                    "attrs": {
                      "resourceId": "108482",
                      "resourceType": "BiblicaStudyNotesKeyTerms"
                    }
                  }
                ],
                "text": "Asa"
              },
              {
                "type": "text",
                "text": " led God’s people the way that kings were supposed to. The rules about kings were recorded in Deuteronomy 17:14–20."
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "paragraph",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "text",
                "text": "Asa led the southern kingdom in worshipping only God and obeying the "
              },
              {
                "type": "text",
                "marks": [
                  {
                    "type": "resourceReference",
                    "attrs": {
                      "resourceId": "108335",
                      "resourceType": "BiblicaStudyNotesKeyTerms"
                    }
                  }
                ],
                "text": "Law of Moses"
              },
              {
                "type": "text",
                "text": ". He trusted God to save the southern kingdom when they were attacked. He listened to the prophet Azariah and obeyed his message. Asa led the people to commit again to being faithful to God’s "
              },
              {
                "type": "text",
                "marks": [
                  {
                    "type": "resourceReference",
                    "attrs": {
                      "resourceId": "108237",
                      "resourceType": "BiblicaStudyNotesKeyTerms"
                    }
                  }
                ],
                "text": "covenant"
              },
              {
                "type": "text",
                "text": " with them."
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "paragraph",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "text",
                "text": "But when he was older he stopped leading the way kings should lead. Asa didn’t trust God to save the southern kingdom from Baasha and the northern kingdom. He put the prophet Hanani in prison for speaking God’s messages against him. Asa treated God’s people badly. He didn’t ask God for help when he had a problem with his feet."
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "paragraph",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "text",
                "text": "Because of these things, the southern kingdom didn’t have "
              },
              {
                "type": "text",
                "marks": [
                  {
                    "type": "resourceReference",
                    "attrs": {
                      "resourceId": "108211",
                      "resourceType": "BiblicaStudyNotesKeyTerms"
                    }
                  }
                ],
                "text": "peace"
              },
              {
                "type": "text",
                "text": " and "
              },
              {
                "type": "text",
                "marks": [
                  {
                    "type": "resourceReference",
                    "attrs": {
                      "resourceId": "108212",
                      "resourceType": "BiblicaStudyNotesKeyTerms"
                    }
                  }
                ],
                "text": "rest"
              },
              {
                "type": "text",
                "text": ". They were always at war. That was how God brought "
              },
              {
                "type": "text",
                "marks": [
                  {
                    "type": "resourceReference",
                    "attrs": {
                      "resourceId": "108233",
                      "resourceType": "BiblicaStudyNotesKeyTerms"
                    }
                  }
                ],
                "text": "judgement"
              },
              {
                "type": "text",
                "text": " against Asa for his "
              },
              {
                "type": "text",
                "marks": [
                  {
                    "type": "resourceReference",
                    "attrs": {
                      "resourceId": "108195",
                      "resourceType": "BiblicaStudyNotesKeyTerms"
                    }
                  }
                ],
                "text": "sins"
              },
              {
                "type": "text",
                "text": "."
              }
            ]
          }
        ]
      }
    }
  ],
